
Name: Tic Tac Toe
Alternate Names: Xs and Ox, Noughts and Crosses, Naughts and Crosses

Played on a Board with a 3x3 grid.
Two Player game.
 - One Player has Markers with a visible 'X'.
 - The other Player has Markers with a visible 'O'.
 - There is no agreeded upon rule for which Player goes first (Xs or Os).
 
Board starts out empty.
Players take turns where they each place down a single Marker into an empty grid space during their turn.
 - Each grid space accepts one and only one Marker.
Win Condition: Player manages to place three of their markers in the same column, same row, or same diagonal.
If the game can no longer progress (due to all grid spaces being filled), then it is a draw.
 - Draws are often called a, "cat's game."
